                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="28v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100481"> Birgitta Birgersdotter </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Regula salvatoris (The Birgittine Rule, the third-person version)</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit regula Sancti Saluatoris a sede apostolica pro constitutionibus approbata et confirmata de humilitate castitate et paupertate Capitulum primum</rubric>
                                <incipit>Principium itaque huius religionis et salutis</incipit>
                                <explicit>quod terra sunt et in terram reuertentur</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit regula sanctissima domini nostri Ihesu christi Saluatoris</finalRubric>
                                <note>The text corresponds the the sigma version edited by Eklund, excluding, however, the bull of Urban VI.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107122">Eklund (1975)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="140" to="172" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="29r" to="32v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Revelations regarding the Birgittine rule</title>
                                <rubric>Secuntur aliquae reuelationes <del>sy</del> super regulam et statuta pertinentes et primo de organis non habendis in monasteryo</rubric>
                                <incipit>Cristus loquitur sancte Birgitte fily israel quia carnales erant</incipit>
                                <explicit>in duabus septimanis si expedit saluti et cetera</explicit>
                                <note>The section contains chapter X, XIII, XIV, XV and XXIII of the Revelationes extravagantes.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107126">Hollman (1956)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="113" to="232" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="32v" to="38v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102589">Nicolaus Hermanni</persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Office for St Birgitta</title>
                                <rubric>Sequitur historia de sancta Birgitta matris nostre de eius veneracione In i vesperis antiphone super psalmos feriales</rubric>
                                <incipit>Rosa rorans bonitatem</incipit>
                                <explicit>et recte viuendi nobis operentur effectum per dominum etc</explicit>
                                <note>The office ends with a mass for the commemoration of St Birgitta (<locus from="37r" to="38v" scheme="folios"/>). A detailed inventory of the contents of the office is given by <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107275">Collijn (1945)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="12" to="12" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107287">Lundén (1971)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="77" to="110" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="39r" to="79r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102590"> Birger Gregersson </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Office for St Birgitta</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="39r" to="45v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Office with mass</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipit hystoria in solemnitatibus Sancte Birgitte de regno Suecie antiphona in primis vesperis psalmus</rubric>
                                    <incipit>Omnia laudate Birgitte matris inclite festa iocunda suscipe</incipit>
                                    <explicit>oratio in cuius veneratione hec tue obtulimus maiestati per dominum nostrum etc</explicit>
                                    <note>The office ends with a mass for the commemoration of St Birgitta (<locus from="44r" to="45v" scheme="folios"/>). A detailed inventory of the contents of the office is given by <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107275">Collijn (1945)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="13" to="13" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>.</note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="45v" to="79r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Life of St Birgitta </title>
                                    <rubric>Sequitur legenda de sancta Birgitta</rubric>
                                    <incipit>Ecce descripsi eam tibi tripliciter</incipit>
                                    <explicit>eam venerandam declarat et mirificat dominus noster Ihesus christus qui est benedictus in secula seculorum Amen</explicit>
                                    <finalRubric>Explicit hystoria cum legenda sancte Birgitte de regno suecie compilata per venerabilem patrem dominum Birgerum Archiepiscopum Upsalensem scripta in monasteryo Marie may<supplied reason="omitted">hingen</supplied> ordinis sancti Saluatoris Et est sciendum quod ter in anno habetur festum de eadem sancta Birgitta videlicet Natale quando scilicet defuncta est quod cadit in proxima die post festum sancte marie magdalene que est x kalendas augusti secundum eius festum est translacione quando scilicet translata est de roma ad partes Suecie quod cadit xxviii die mensis May tertium vero eius festum est canonizacionis quod cadit iiii die mensis octobris etc </finalRubric>
                                </msItem>
                                <note>The life of St Birgitta, constituting the readings of Birger Gregersson's office, has sometimes been transmitted independently of the rest of the office (see <bibl>
                                        <title type="uniform" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107186">Undhagen</title>
                                        <citedRange from="31" to="35" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>) and is transmitted here as a separate item.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107186">Undhagen (1960)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="177" to="237" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="79r" to="97v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Canonization bull of Boniface IX</title>
                                <rubric>Sequitur bulla canonizacionis Sancte Birgitte matris nostre</rubric>
                                <incipit>Bonifacius <add place="above">IX</add> episcopus seruus seruorum dei venerabilibus fratribus</incipit>
                                <explicit>gaudia peruenire Datum rome aput sanctum Petrum nonis octobris pontificatus nostri anno secundo</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        The bull ends with the colophon of the confirmation of Pope Martinus V, dated here 15 July 1419 (cf. <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107159">BHL</title>
                                            <citedRange from="1347" to="1347" unit="number"/>
                                        </bibl>): <quote>Nulli ergo omnino hominum liceat hanc pacinam nostre approbationis confirmationis et communicionis infringere vel ei ausu temerario contraire Si quis autem hoc attemptare presumpserit indignacionem omnipotentis dei et beatorum petri et pauli apostolorum eius se noverit incursurum Datum florencie in idibus July pontificatus nostri anno 2:o</quote> (Cf. <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107125">SDHK</title>
                                            <citedRange from="19312" to="19312" unit="number"/>
                                        </bibl>) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="98r" to="104v" scheme="folios"/> blank.</p>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107281">Tomassetti (1859)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="616" to="624" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
